metadata.name: Tessellum #14
metadata.description:
Tessellum can be understood as a sophisticated form of tessellation that combines repetitive geometric patterns with spatial coherence and depth. In an artistic context, it suggests a structured configuration where each component interlocks precisely, creating a seamless, continuous design. This term embodies not only visual repetition but also a sense of order and interconnectedness, where patterns are arranged in such a way that they convey both structural complexity and a harmonious, multidimensional effect.

The **Tessellum** project is essentially a unique cube. It‚Äôs a cube that has other cubes on each of its faces, arranged in such a way that they do not collide with each other. It can be described as a combination of cubes of various sizes, forming the final image. In this project, you can rotate the main cube as you wish by clicking and holding the left mouse button.
this project available in both TEZ&ETH

metadata.name: Primitifs syst√©matiques #90
metadata.description:
Primitifs syst√©matiques is the first generative instalment of David Umemoto‚Äôs studies of space and volume. Placed at the crux of brutalism and minimalism, these structures based on the original stackable concrete piece Primitif 04 evoke impossible paths yet to be explored. 

The original Primitif 04 has been both preserved and dented, conserved and enhanced. It is still here. But it cannot be found, only encountered. Throughout your explorations of the Primitifs syst√©matiques, you will find that its original shapes have been multiplied, rotated, re-ordered to create new structures. After spending some time exploring its paths, when you stop looking for it, you will realize that 04 is still here, intact.

Lines of work chosen for this piece also draw a perspective. The orientation of the primitives pulls directly towards an intense source of light. Sometimes it is visible, sometimes it is not. This perfect alignment is a call to life. They who look at the sunrise with relief cannot be anything but hopeful. But how can we project life on a concrete behemoth? Stand long enough in front of it, and you too will see that we have no choice but to.

----

Primitifs syst√©matiques is the generative art genesis piece of David Umemoto. It was built in collaboration with Anaglyphic. It is the first collaborative spatial token made available on the anaver.se.

metadata.name: f-emerald #222
metadata.description:
f-emerald generates unique ephemeral crystal-like structures that morph in space. each generation has a different shape, animation and colour palette. 

the crystals flicker with colours in the dark most of the time. there is, however, a 20% chance of obtaining a crystal on a bright background with a light colour palette and one out of ten structures is created in black and white.

metadata.name: Organic Diffusion #152
metadata.description:
Organic diffusion, a silent guide,
Through the veils of chaos, we abide.
In the microscopic realm, secrets unfold,
A journey of mystery, yet untold...

Display : Organic diffusion adapts by default to any screen, with an artwork changing depending on width and height (while maintaining the same parameters). In Vertical mode, the artwork displayed will be the captured (preview) one. Meant to be displayed on walls for an extended period, allowing enjoyment of the ever-changing artwork...

First minter gets 25% of royalties.

Options :
p to pause/unpause
s to save
1, 2, ... to increase the resolution (3 to get 3000pixels in height, etc...)
c to capture the same preview
d to toggle display between fullscreen and vertical (4:3)
+/- to increase/decrease details
z to zoom-in
f to increase some speed
v to start/stop the webm video capture
a in live view will allow to capture the 1000 seeds in low res images to help you choose your favorites

metadata.name: Murked Being #81
metadata.description:
This artwork was part of experimentation to create a figure that implements the pareidolia effect with feedback modulation and other manipulation using the Hydra library. The visual appearance was inspired by Banaspati, one of many ghostly entities in Indonesia that looks like a floating fireball. The being was visualized to look as it was formed from blazing dark smoke with some parts showing sharp-subtle shapes, colors, and textures, creating a sense of abstract-ghoulish expression that is murked in its impression.

Move your mouse up and down to rotate the eyes and the hidden animation on its head.‚Ä®‚Ä®Made using Hydra (https://hydra.ojack.xyz/)

Rangga Purnama Aji, 2022
https://linktr.ee/ranggapuraji

metadata.name: Cosmic Type #27
metadata.description:
Cosmic Type is a kinetic type experiment that explores both graphic space as structural and semantic agency. Inspired by the early pioneering work of the concrete poets such as Dom Sylvester Hou√©dard, Ian Hamilton Finley and Steve McCaffe, the project is a play with letters, words and graphic form in the computational and generative space.

Each iteration gives you the possibility to discover a variety of visual form through exploring the system. Please explore your iteration with the key interactions below. It is hoped that you give the time to explore and observe. If you don't, you may end up with just a blank canvas. 

Thank you for collecting. 

Key Interactions

‚Äòa‚Äô activates forward motion on/off
‚Äòb‚Äô activates backward motion on/off
‚Äòr‚Äô rotates grid 45¬∞ [ rotates on key pressed]
‚Äòf‚Äô rotates the grid freely [ stops on key release ]
‚Äòp‚Äô switches grid scale on/off [ this can be CPU heavy on older machines ] 
‚Äòg‚Äô extra glyphs on/off
‚Äòq‚Äô return to the initial state 


Program written by Mark Webster

metadata.name: Pobbles #96
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

‚Ä¢ The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
‚Ä¢ See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
‚Ä¢ Alternative titles considered include Peggles‚Ñ¢, Plops‚Ñ¢, Blobbies‚Ñ¢, Floofs‚Ñ¢, Flintstones‚Ñ¢, Lardies‚Ñ¢, Plumps‚Ñ¢, Fats‚Ñ¢ and Wet-Ones‚Ñ¢. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
‚Ä¢ They work well with toddlers.

metadata.name: Heliks #37
metadata.description:
To bid farewell to fx(hash) 1.0, I prepared this piece based on the intro "Random Generation", which I coded for the demogroup Latitude Independent Association and was awarded second place in the 4k intro compo at the Revision 2023 demoparty. 

The centerpiece is an interpretation of a strange star surrounded by helicoidal surfaces, animated with a smooth and steady motion, contributing to a sense of harmony and continuity.

This work was designed and developed using various techniques within a fragment shader, allowing me to explore and experiment with the properties of light and motion. My aim was to create something that captured both the dynamic energy of the surface and the elegance of the moving helicoidal surfaces, always striving to maintain a balance between technical complexity and visual aesthetics.

The piece is somewhat demanding on the GPU and is not designed for mobile devices or old, low-end GPUs.
